metadata.name: Humanity #30
metadata.description:
In a modern society everyone tries to dictate his own rules of life, where is no place for emotions and sincere feelings. Those concrete jungles are more like giant anthills.
People are interchangeable gears in one big mechanism, today you are here and tomorrow.. who knows. Tomorrow you could be gone.

New element, same functionality, you won`t find something new. Humanity is on the right path to globalization and unification. We are entitled to agreed points.
You can`t be who you are. Sooner or later, you`re going to have to be an interchangeable element. 
The rules of this life have been written for you.

Polina Arz ¬©

A professional Fashion designer and fashion artist whose work reflects the spirit of modernity and the world around us in the language of current trends and contemporary art.

metadata.name: Permutation City #8
metadata.description:
The work is inspired by the novel Permutation City by Greg Egan, the author of the hard science fiction.

It raises the issue of whether we can in principle understand that we exist in reality or in a simulation.

According to the Theory of Dust (which is described in the novel), the universe is simulatable and all other possible universes are equally as real as ours, emerging spontaneously from their own mathematical self-consistency. Human consciousness is¬†Turing-computable, which means that consciousness can be also produced by a computer program.

The¬†Autoverse¬†is an¬†artificial life¬†simulator, a massive complex cellular automaton universe, producing cities and the consciousness of human copies.

Gradually, due to failures and a lack of computing power, the idea of the reliability of such universes is destroyed. 

Spaces crumble, cities become fluid and drain down, turning into dust and digital glitch.

Thanks to Yulikolay for helping with code, using p5.Riso.js library for generating files suitable for risograph printing.
Source images for permutation cities are made with a help of DALL¬∑E mini neural network.

metadata.name: The resolution of chaos #17
metadata.description:
Chaos in physics is not synonymous with absolute disorder: elegant geometrical structures describe the behavior of chaotic systems. Chaos limits the predictability, but also makes causal relations appear where we did not imagine them.
Made with P5

metadata.name: Penumbra #135
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)

metadata.name: Colorfall #22
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.
